# only adding genre to the nonlinmulmod2
model7 = mod = lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+genre, data = subsetmovie2)

# only adding rating
model8 = lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+rating,data = subsetmovie2)

# only adding top director
model9 = lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+topdirector,data = subsetmovie2)

# only adding top 100 actors 
model10 = lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+top100star,data = subsetmovie2)

# only adding top100 actress  
model11 = lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+top100stress,data = subsetmovie2)

#adding both top 100 actors and top 100 actors
model12 = lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+top100star+top100stress,data = subsetmovie2)

#adding genre, rating, top100 actors, top100 actress
model13 =  lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+genre+rating+top100star+top100stress,data = subsetmovie2)

#adding genre, rating, top100 actors, top100 actress, and the interactions between genre and top 100 actors/ top 100 actress( the reason is to see if top actors and top actress would have different on diffrent genres)
model14 = lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+genre+rating+top100star+top100stress+genre*top100star+genre*top100stress, data = subsetmovie2)

#adding genre, rating, top100 actors, top100 actress, top 10 directors
model15 = lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+genre+rating+top100star+top100stress+topdirector, data = subsetmovie2)

#adding genre, rating, top100 actors, top100 actress, top 10 directors, and interaction terms 
model16 = lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+genre+rating+top100star+top100stress+topdirector+genre*top100star+genre*top100stress, data = subsetmovie2)

#adding genre, rating, top100 actors, top100 actress, top 10 directors, and interaction terms. Three interaction terms: genre*top100star+genre*top100stress+topdirector*genre
model17 = lm(avg_imdb_tmdb_score~poly(votes_1,5)+runtime+year_22+month+profit+genre+rating+top100star+top100stress+topdirector+genre*top100star+genre*top100stress+topdirector*genre, data = subsetmovie2)
